'''''Star Wars'' 18''' is the eighteenth issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Archie Goodwin]], illustrated by [[Carmine Infantino]] and [[Gene Day]], and first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[September 26]], [[1978]]. It features the story "'''The Empire Strikes!'''," in which the [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|Heroes of Yavin]] arrive at [[The Wheel/Legends|the Wheel]], a nefarious [[Space station/Legends|space station]] associated with the [[House of Tagge/Legends|House of Tagge]].

==Publisher's summary==
''What has caused Luke to fall into a coma?''

==Plot summary==
While training on board the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], Luke Skywalker falls into a deep and mysterious trance. As [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] the ''Falcon'' toward medical help, they stumble across the remains of a [[House of Tagge/Legends|House of Tagge]] [[Merchant/Legends|merchant]] [[Starship/Legends|ship]]. They discover a surviving [[Unidentified Rebel soldier (The Wheel)|Rebel soldier]] who tells them that the Tagge ship was actually attacked by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]], but it was made to look like [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] had destroyed the craft. The Imperial [[Cruiser/Legends|cruiser]] of [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Zertik Strom/Legends|Strom]] soon arrives on the scene intending to capture the ''Falcon'' and her crew, but Han pilots their escape to the relative safety of [[The Wheel/Legends|the Wheel]]. Strom sends his troops to follow, but is soon contacted by the Wheel's administrator [[Simon Greyshade/Legends|Simon Greyshade]], who reminds the Imperial commander that the Wheel is supposed to be free of interference from the Empire. Strom then claims that these Rebels are responsible for the attack on the House of Tagge ship which was carrying profits from the Wheel, at which point Greyshade relents and allows the Imperials onto the Wheel's lower levels to catch the Rebels.

